Package: gothouant
Title: Kinematics of Hymenopteran Locomotion from Tracker Files
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Toni", "Wöhrl", 
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Tools for project‑specific processing and analysis of stride-wise gait kinematics in walking insects, developed as a data-processing methods companion for the article “Go thou to the ant: A comparative analysis of locomotion in a phylogenetically diverse sample of Hymenoptera (Hexapoda)”. The package supports importing trajectories from ‘.trk’ files generated by the Tracker software (https://opensourcephysics.github.io/tracker-website/aggregation), extracting multi‑leg recordings into per‑stride and per‑cycle measures, and visualizing gait metrics and tripod geometries. It further provides workflows for statistical modelling using linear mixed‑effects models (via ‘lme4’) to quantify differences between ants and non‑ant arthropods while accounting for repeated measures within individuals and species.
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    XML
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
